profile:
The decision to buy a home is seldom easy.  It's major, complex and very personal.  Along with the consideration of price and the various appeals of the neighbourhood, style, size and floor plan, the fundamental question arises - is the house itself sound?  What kinds of repairs may be in order, and what can reasonably be expected in the way of costs?

The decision to purchase, and in some cases the purchase price, may be affected by all these factors and we can give you the answers.
